3. License Tiers

   You may use the Software only under one of the tiers below. If more than
   one tier could apply, the most restrictive tier that you do not satisfy
   controls.

   3.1 Personal License

   Licensor grants a natural person a limited, non-exclusive,
   non-transferable, non-sublicensable, revocable license to install and
   use one Authorized Copy of the Software for Personal Use only.

   Personal Use does not include use on behalf of an Organization, use in
   the course of employment or contract work, or any Commercial Use.

   3.2 Small Team License

   Licensor grants an Organization a limited, non-exclusive,
   non-transferable, non-sublicensable, revocable license to install and
   use Authorized Copies of the Software for Commercial Use, provided that
   the Organization does not exceed the Small Team Limit of Licensed
   Developers at any time.

   Each Licensed Developer must be a named individual. You may not rotate,
   share, or pool accounts or installations among multiple people to stay
   within the Small Team Limit.

   3.3 Commercial License (Per Seat)

   If your Organization has more than the Small Team Limit of Licensed
   Developers, or if Licensor otherwise requires it, Commercial Use
   requires a Commercial License Agreement with Licensor on a per-seat
   basis—one paid seat for each Licensed Developer.

   Licensor expressly reserves the right to offer, sell, license, and
   distribute the Software, derivative works, and related services on
   commercial terms, including per-seat pricing, volume discounts, and
   enterprise agreements.

4. Counting Licensed Developers

   Count every individual in an Organization who uses the Software, even
   occasionally. Contractors, consultants, and temporary staff who use the
   Software while working for or with the Organization count toward the
   limit.

   Automated systems, build agents, and shared service accounts do not
   count as Licensed Developers unless a human uses the Software through
   that account as their primary means of access.

